	<main>
		<img width="2500" height="1201" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-the-grind.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="blood in bay in the Faroe Islands" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-the-grind.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-the-grind-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-the-grind-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-the-grind-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-the-grind-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-the-grind-2048x984.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-the-grind-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">During a grindadráp, water in the bay turns red with the blood of freshly killed whales. Photo by Eyðfinnur Olsen/Alamy Stock Photo</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">Blood in the Water, Food on the Table, Protesters on the Shore</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">A centuries-old traditional whale hunt in the Faroe Islands remains in the crosshairs of animal rights activists.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/paige-cromley/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Paige Cromley</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
